                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable S</hi> 76.) On the 13th of June, at about two o'clock in the morning, I stopped the prisoner—he had these boots with him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was in Brentford on the Saturday night; I gave a man half-a-crown for these boots; he said they were his own; I was going across the field, and met the policeman, who charged me with stealing them.</p>
